<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
This species was described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Geocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geocoris elegantulus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Geocoris elegantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930409487068" author="Distant, WL" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B3" refString="Distant, WL, 1904. Rhynchotal Notes. XXII. Heteroptera from North Queensland. Annals &amp; Magazine of Natural History 1, Series 7, 3(7): 263-276. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930409487068" title="Rhynchotal Notes. XXII. Heteroptera from North Queensland. Annals &amp; Magazine of Natural History 1, Series 7, 3 (7): 263 - 276." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930409487068" year="1904">Distant 1904</bibRefCitation>
) and cited as such by subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" author="Malipatil, MB" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="299 - 327" refId="B10" refString="Malipatil, MB, 1994. Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae). Invertebrate Systematics 8 (2): 299 - 327, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" title="Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" volume="8" year="1994">Malipatil 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cassis, G" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B1" refString="Cassis, G, Gross, G, 2002. Hemiptera: Heteroptera (Pentatomomorpha). In: Houston WWK, Wells A (Eds) Zoological Catalogue of Australia, Volume 27.3 B. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne" title="Hemiptera: Heteroptera (Pentatomomorpha). In: Houston WWK, Wells A (Eds) Zoological Catalogue of Australia, Volume 27.3 B." year="2002">Cassis and Gross 2002</bibRefCitation>
). A careful examination of both type and non-type specimens available concluded that the species displays synapomorphies used to define 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobor" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Umbrageocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Umbrageocoris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Umbrageocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the presence of a median groove on vertex, a Y- or cup-shaped labial trough, and the arrangement of sutures at abdominal tergites 4/5 and 5/6, thus the following new combination is here proposed: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kóbor" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Umbrageocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Umbrageocoris elegantulus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Umbrageocoris elegantulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Distant, 1904), comb. nov.
</paragraph>
